{"questionId":"c9417793","correctAnswer":"18","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Solve the equation","content":"Subtract 45: $|x-9|=18$. So $x-9=18$ or $x-9=-18$, giving $x=27$ or $x=-9$."},{"title":"Sum the solutions","content":"Add: $27+(-9)=18$. (Shortcut: $|x-a|=b$ gives sum $2a=18$.)<br/><br/>The answer is <strong>18</strong>."}]}